  "reducer_contract_for_wp07b": [
    "Only the application reducer may mutate durable project authority.",
    "Validate a command completely before mutation; rejection is atomic.",
    "One effective durable command advances the project revision exactly once.",
    "A semantic no-op does not advance the revision or mark the project dirty.",
    "Transient, runtime, and diagnostic changes never advance the project revision.",
    "Commands, events, snapshots, task IDs, and faults are typed and framework-neutral.",
    "Asynchronous completion is admitted only when its source identity, operation identity, and currentness generation still match.",
    "Missing typed IDs fail explicitly; no index, name, or legacy-format fallback is permitted.",
    "Layer membership, order, preset closure, artifact references, and project-bound revisions remain valid after every accepted transition."
  ],
